&lt;p&gt;This artical will show you how to connect to your android, so you can play with your android via adb&lt;sup id="fnref:1"&gt;&lt;a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="setup-your-environment"&gt;Setup your environment&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="get-android-sdk-platform-tools"&gt;get Android SDK Platform Tools&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;download &lt;a href="https://developer.android.com/studio/releases/platform-tools"&gt;platform-tools&lt;/a&gt; directly or install it with your package manager:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# arch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo pacman -Sy android-tools
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="enable-debugging"&gt;enable debugging&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;first enable developer mode, for my op6, clicking the build number a bunch of times enables developer mode&lt;/p&gt;
